>>>	cdate_liam_1
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			The Redemption Arc Program
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	default	Well, the thing is... I did terrible things back when I was a dark lord, you know?	
	liam	cleaning	I... I've made lots of effort to make sure I've changed since then.	Lex_thinking
	liam	sideface	But regret alone doesn't make up for the atrocities I inflicted, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%.
	player	sorry	Oh, Liam... you're being too hard on yourself.
	liam	sad	I foisted death and destruction upon thousands of people...	
	player	animesweat	Ah... okay, maybe you're being the right amount of hard.	Player_bench_yikes
	player	default
	liam	explaining	Ha... yes. So, I spent countless nights devising a plan to enact change. Meaningful change.	
	liam	default	Then it hit me: I joined the Coven, which was one of the biggest changes in my life.	
	liam	cleaning	In a way, Joy and the others rescued me from the dark place I was in.	
	player	thinking	That does sound like meaningful change.
	liam	nostalgic	It truly was.
	liam	default	And it made me realize that there was something I could contribute.	Lex_excited
	liam	sideface	I have a unique perspective on what it's like to be in such a dark place, and what it's like to come back from it.
	liam	smirk	So, what if I could build a program to do the same for other villains?	Lex_smile
	liam	thinking	And, look... I won't pretend that it's that simple. There's nuance to it, and it's surely quite a complicated topic...
	liam	sideface	I don't mean to pretend that the program brushes off the damage we've done.	
	liam	default	It's not enough -- it'll never be enough -- but still, doing something is better than doing nothing at all.	Lex_default
	player	lookingdown	Yeah, I get that.	Player_bench_makessense
	player	thinking	Still... if these powerful beings are helping to save the world instead of trying to destroy it...
	player	affirming	...that surely is meaningful change, no?
	liam	sideface	I hope so...
	narrator		You both remain quiet for some time. Liam seems like he's looking inwards, navigating all his thoughts and regrets.	
	narrator		And maybe the best you can do right now is just hold his hand through this silence.	

>>>	cdate_liam_2
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			Being a TTRPG game master	
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	smirk	Ah, yes... my latest journey into a new art form!	L_ahyes
	liam	explaining	It's like writing an adventure, and like directing a play too...
	liam	explaining	...and yet, it's also conducting an orchestra of characters you have to make play in symphony.
	player	teasing	So you're saying that Game Master Liam de Lioncourt is what you get when you fuse Tolkien, Shakespeare, and Mozart?	Player_bench_hehe
	liam	smirk	I know you're being sarcastic... but yes, pretty much.
	liam	prideful	You're weaving an ever-evolving narrative that must adapt by the minute to the choices of everyone involved.
	liam	smirk	You invest countless hours to ensure the maximum thrill and enjoyment of your players.
	player	surprised	That sounds... dedicated.	Player_bench_questionreally
	liam	cleaning	%CURRENTPLAYERNAME%, when I get passionate about something, I surrender my mind and body with no concessions.
	liam	glasses	In more mundane words: life is not there to be half-assed.	Lex_glasses
	player	blush	Anyone would be lucky to get... involved in your passions.
	liam	smirk	Your words, not mine.
	liam	explaining	But yes, to sum it up: I try to create narratives that immerse my players in unique situations that they wouldn't experience otherwise.
	liam	prideful	For instance, I recently ran a campaign in which my players were the head priests of a deity that ruled over one of the cardinal sins.	Lex_talking
	liam	explaining	They had to travel the lands, growing their cult and sowing chaos, as they lured mortals into a sinful existence.
	liam	smirk	We played three sets of campaigns, with them changing into priests of a different cardinal sin.
	player	surprised	I gotta admit, it makes me wanna try it at least.	Player_bench_oooh
	liam	nostalgic	Yes, it's a shame you weren't there. It was a thing of wonder, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%.
	liam	glasses	Ah, I once again rejoice at finding a new art form for me to master!
	player	teasing	I'm sure it's also a plus that it's one that forces a group of people to listen to you for hours.	Player_bench_hehe
	liam	facepalm	Oh, shut up!
	liam	smirk	(But yes, that is indeed a plus.)
	narrator		You ask Liam to describe to you some of the campaigns he's designed so far.	
	narrator		He glows when he talks of something he's passionate about. It's... quite nice.	

>>>	cdate_liam_3
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			Being the inspiration for "Liam Prom"
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	smirk	What a thing, eh?	
	liam	glasses	The artist becomes the muse!	Lex_glasses
	liam	explaining	I guess if you live long enough, it's no surprise someone ends up telling the story of you.	
	player	thinking	And the story of Liam is one of dozens of Liams going through life while attending Liam Academy?	
	liam	thinking	It is... a choice, certainly.	Lex_thinking
	liam	eyeroll	It's clear that Zoe and I have quite different understandings on what constitutes art.
	liam	cleaning	But I've chosen not to bother her too much with my opinions of her work.
	player	lookingdown	That's nice of you.
	liam	sideface	I would never want to be the one to cut the wings of an artist.
	player	asking	Are your visions that different, really?
	player	thinking	Sure, "Liam Prom" falls in a very different category than your conceptual poetry...
	player	teasing	...but is it that different from... let's say, "2 Guys 1 Salad"?	Player_bench_hehe
	player	default
	liam	surprised	...
	liam	smirk	...Well, you got me there.
	liam	default	In any case, I really appreciated that this time, Zoe consulted me first to see if I was okay with her project idea.	Lex_default
	player	asking	What's your favorite part of it?
	liam	nostalgic	You'll laugh at how Liam this will sound... but I think it's her just asking about me and... like... really listening.	
	liam	cleaning	She has to milk dozens of Liams out of me, right?	
	player	teasing	Hehe... "she has to milk dozens of Liams."	Player_bench_hehe
	liam	default	%CURRENTPLAYERNAME%! Anyway... to do so, she'll sit and interview me for hours.
	liam	explaining	Of course, we've known each other for a couple years now; but I think, silly as it is, "Liam Prom" has brought us closer.
	player	smilinginlove	I'm glad to hear that, Liam. I guess we all like to feel seen, don't we?
	liam	nostalgic	...It is a nice, warm feeling, yes.	Lex_blushside
	narrator		You two then share some quiet. Maybe you're causing a bit of that nice, warm feeling in him, too.	

>>>	cdate_liam_4
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			Sharing an apartment
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	thinking	...What?	L_questionwhat
	liam	thinking	You want to... live with me?
	player	animesweat	No, you dumb-dumb!
	player	default	I meant how's the experience of sharing an apartment going.
	player	thinking	I heard you're living with Omen these days, right?
	liam	smirk	Ah! Yes, I am.
	liam	cleaning	I'm her sponsor in the Redemption Arc Program.	Lex_talking
	liam	sideface	And since she was imprisoned for more than a century, Omen... well... she had nowhere to go.
	liam	default	The plan is she'll eventually find a place of her own, but until then, she can crash with me.
	player	asking	Not gonna lie: that's super thoughtful of you. But knowing Omen, I can't help but wonder: how is it going so far?	Player_bench_nice
	liam	eyeroll	Well... it's not that different from giving a stray cat a home...
	liam	facepalm	...if the stray cat somehow knew how to operate a chainsaw.	Lex_eyeroll
	player	yikes	Yeah, that does sound like Omen.
	player	default
	liam	sideface	Still, like with a stray cat, it doesn't matter that the cat has trust issues and is prone to wreak havoc: you still try to make them feel at home.
	liam	eyeroll	I've tried to curry Omen's favor by astounding her with my superior cuisine, but she seems to have... a less refined palate.
	liam	cleaning	After some trial and error, I've learned she has a soft spot for hot dogs. So, hot dogs it is.
	player	affirming	Liam! I always thought having a pet could help soften up that obnoxious, stuck-up exterior of yours...
	player	teasing	...I just never imagined that your ideal pet would be an evil overlord.	Player_bench_hehe
	liam	surprised	%CURRENTPLAYERNAME%!
	player	thinking	I mean, I'm not implying Omen is a pet to you... maybe more of an annoying little sibling?	
	player	affirming	In any case, I'm sure you get my point.
	liam	smirk	Hehe... I do.	Lex_smile
	liam	sideface	I just hope Omen can learn that there's a better way to do things, other than murder and evil...
	narrator		It's heartwarming to see Liam take his sponsor role so seriously and care this much for another person.	
	narrator		He seems to really understand the importance of redemption.

>>>	cdate_liam_5
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			How's the con so far?
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	cleaning	It's been quite good so far.	
	liam	default	I spend a good portion of the day in my yaoi booth, in the artists' alley. That can get a bit exhausting.
	player	teasing	The masses crave their drawings of men kissing.
	liam	smirk	They surely do.	Lex_smile
	liam	explaining	Luckily, some of our friends sometimes come by, either to give me some company or help me man the booth.
	player	asking	Ah, yeah. I think I saw April there yesterday, right?
	liam	default	Yes, she stayed for a couple hours.	Lex_default
	liam	smirk	She really knows how to keep the crowd entertained.
	liam	prideful	I offered to help her in exchange. I'm sure she could benefit from my expertise in songwriting and general knowledge of the arts.
	liam	surprised	Surprisingly, she said it wasn't necessary!
	player	default	Yeah... surprisingly.	Player_bench_yeah
	liam	eyeroll	Instead, she asked me to draw her squashed between a couple muscular men. To each their own taste, I suppose.	
	liam	explaining	In any case, I don't spend the whole day at the booth, either.
	liam	glasses	I've been hunting for rare gachapon with Doug. We're like avid explorers, trying to capture elusive specimens.	Lex_glasses
	player	affirming	I'd watch a reality show of you two going on your little explorer adventure!	
	liam	smirk	Why not watch it live? Come with us next time.
	player	blush	Oh, I'd love to!	Player_bench_sure
	liam	nostalgic	But yeah... it's been a good time.
	liam	prideful	Sometimes even Liam de Lioncourt must indulge in his lowest-brow passions.
	narrator		And you wanna join him in such low-brow passions! You both check the con's schedule to see what you can do together the next day.	

>>>	cdate_liam_6
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	liam
>action			The Spooky Con friend group
>layout	duo	liam,player
	liam	default	You mean, how was the group formed?	
	liam	cleaning	Well, Zoe and I know each other from Spooky Academy, of course.	
	liam	thinking	Doug, I met through Zoe... and then April through Doug...	Lex_thinking
	liam	explaining	I was the one who brought Omen into the mix, as I'm their sponsor for the Redemption Arc Program.	
	liam	default	I try to keep her close while she goes through her first steps of the program, so I convinced her to join us for the con.
	player	default	That was nice of you.
	liam	sideface	Maybe. I just think that building good relationships can help her realize there's a better way of doing things. It was key for me, at least.	Lex_blushside
	player	blush	Good relationships... like me?
	liam	smirk	Hehe... sure, like you.
	player	thinking	Okay, so there's only Nico left.
	liam	eyeroll	You could say I brought Nico along, although it'd be more accurate to say Nico inserted themself into the group.	Lex_eyeroll
	player	surprised	Wait... what?
	liam	prideful	Not so long ago, I started attending some improv classes, in order to perfect my thespian skills.
	liam	cleaning	Nico attended that class too, and... well, they're quite the extrovert, you know?
	liam	sideface	They sort of befriended everyone in the class except me.
	liam	eyeroll	They tried, but I politely rejected their friendly advances. I've made more than enough friends over four centuries.	Lex_bored
	player	teasing	Ah! The unstoppable friendly force versus the immovable unfriendly object.
	liam	default	And I would've won... but alas, one day I was with Zoe and Doug at a café when Nico spotted me from across the street.
	liam	eyeroll	Someone wiser would have understood I wanted to mind my own business... but Nico is surely more charming than they are wise.
	liam	cleaning	They came over to say hi, and before I knew it, they were making plans to meet up with both Zoe and Doug later.
	player	animesweat	You know what? That totally sounds like Nico.	Player_bench_makessense
	liam	nostalgic	It does. And I was irritated at first; but it taught me something:
	liam	nostalgic	It taught me that sometimes, if you're patient, someone you find annoying can become someone you truly appreciate.
	player	teasing	...Like me?
	liam	smirk	Pffft... don't push your luck, you little jester.	Lex_smile
	narrator		Look at you, tearing down Liam's grumpy walls. You keep chatting, and your silly japes steal a few more smiles from him. It's a good sight.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_1
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			Finding success as a creator
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	happy	It's been a ride!	Zex_happy
	zoe	default	Of course, there's a lot of upsides, which are all the ones you can imagine.
	zoe	veryhappy	It's affirming to see so many people connect with what you create, that's for sure.	
	zoe	happy	Writing fanfics for a small, dedicated audience was super fun too, but I can't complain about having a much more sizeable fanbase.
	player	default	Yeah... I imagine "Liam Prom" has opened you to new experiences as a creator.	Player_bench_yeah
	zoe	default	It has. Now I see lots of fans craving a new chapter; writing pages on pages of theories; shipping their favorite Liams...
	player	blush	I personally ship Catboy Maid Liam with Buff Liam.
	zoe	pumped	Ooh, a bit of a crackship! I like that.	Zex_hyped
	zoe	default	But yeah, now I receive much more input, much more praise, much more opportunities...
	player	affirming	That makes me so happy for you!	Player_bench_nice
	zoe	happy	Thanks!
	zoe	thinking	There's still some downsides, though.
	zoe	default	So many people feel connected to "Liam Prom" now. It gives me a sort of responsibility.
	zoe	suspicious	For instance, how could I work on new weird, silly ideas, when the logical thing is to keep expanding this beloved and profitable thing I created?
	player	surprised	You... would prefer NOT to work on "Liam Prom"?
	zoe	suggestive	Nah, I love spending time with my academy of dumb, adorable Liams.
	zoe	thinking	It's just that it gets a bit more complicated.
	zoe	thinking	You start at, "What is the thing I really want to do?"; but the bigger you grow, the more variables chain you.
	zoe	angry	"What's smartest? What's most responsible? What's most profitable?"	Zex_grumpy
	zoe	sad	Bleh, look at me, complaining about... lemme check my notes... "finding success with a project I'm actually quite passionate about."
	player	sorry	Nah, Zoe, it's hella valid to feel stressed.
	zoe	happy	...Thanks.	Zex_blush
	narrator		Zoe and you spend the next few hours decompressing by watching a chill "Cute Girls Doing Cute Things" kind of anime. It proves to be a balm for the soul.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_2
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			All about Liam Prom
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	pumped	My magnum opus!	Zex_hyped
	player	affirming	The Liamest of your works!
	zoe	eyebrows	Pfffft, no doubt.
	player	animesweat	But... and I don't mean this as an offense to Liam... why?	Player_bench_why
	zoe	happy	No, I totally get it. Liam is quite the subject.
	zoe	nostalgic	You know? At Spooky Academy, I observed he wasn't the most popular... and I got the feeling that he's quite the misunderstood character.
	player	teasing	Yeah, I think he has mentioned being misunderstood one or two thousand times.	Player_bench_hehe
	zoe	eyebrows	Yes, he'd say that.
	zoe	thinking	The thing is... I've existed for eons.
	zoe	nostalgic	This change in me wasn't a thing that happened as part of one silly twist when I was asked to prom.
	zoe	nostalgic	I've been observing mortal life for so long... I became enamored with the life I was designed to destroy.
	zoe	default	This fascination grew to the point in which I decided to forfeit most of my power to become part of mortalkind myself.
	player	surprised	That's quite the commitment.
	zoe	default	It is, yes.
	zoe	eyebrows	Every mortal life has incredible stories to tell... even Liam's.
	zoe	suspicious	Sure, Liam is the things he's usually reduced to, like "insufferable" or "a pain in the ass".
	zoe	happy	But he, like any mortal, is so much more.
	zoe	veryhappy	"Liam Prom" is a bit about that: exploring the endless possibilities and the wonderful complexity of every mortal life.	Z_liampromslogan
	player	surprised	Whoa, Zoe... it sounds beautiful when you put it like that.
	player	blush	And here I was, thinking it was mostly about hot Liams kissing and looking hot.
	zoe	suggestive	Well, it can be both, can't it?
	narrator		You spend most of the night discussing what the most beautiful things in life are, and which two Liams would look the hottest kissing.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_3
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			The Redemption Arc Program
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	thinking	Well, it's a bit boring... but, you know? I get it.	
	zoe	blush	We're no saints, so it makes sense to try and make up for all our evil deeds.
	zoe	default	A bunch of us meet up, discuss stuff, and do exercises and all sorts of things Liam has prepared.
	player	default	I'm glad you all are working on exerting meaningful change on yourselves.
	zoe	thinking	Totally! But sometimes it can be a bit of a chore...
	player	thinking	I can imagine. Change takes effort, but I think it's worth it.
	zoe	eyebrows	You betcha, because when we're redeemed enough, we can pass onto the second phase of the program, which is much more epic.	Z_cool
	zoe	happy	The idea is to become a sort of mercenary squad with the goal of helping the Coven!
	zoe	pumped	We'd be redirecting all that power that we harnessed for evil... now repurposed to save the world!
	player	surprised	Okay, that does sound epic.	Player_bench_oooh
	zoe	veryhappy	Right?!
	zoe	default	For now, it's just Liam and I that will soon move into this second phase. The rest have to go to the meetings to prove they're reliable.
	player	affirming	You're an advanced student!
	zoe	veryhappy	Of course! I'm aceing the Redemption Arc Program!
	zoe	veryhappy	I was the most villainous of them all, and now I'm the most redeemed. Top of the class!	Z_fyeah
	zoe	default	They look as grumpy as usual, but I think the Coven is excited to have one of the Old Ones on their side, even if my powers are severely thwarted.
	player	default	Maybe that's what finally tips the balance in favor of mortalkind.
	zoe	happy	Gosh, I hope so!
	zoe	pumped	I also hope we get cool Coven-like uniforms. Imagine that!
	zoe	epiphany	Ah, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%! I just thought: if I become Coven-adjacent... would that count as being a magical girl!?!?	Zex_surprised
	player	teasing	Heh... maybe.
	player	smilinginlove	For what it's worth, you're already a magical girl to me.
	narrator		You spend the following hours brainstorming magical girl catchphrases for Zoe. You feel safe, knowing she will soon be protecting the world.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_4
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			What's next for Zoe?
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	thinking	What a question!	
	player	thinking	I just thought, with "Liam Prom" and all, I can only imagine your future must be looking bright!
	zoe	happy	Yeah, it's wild.	Zex_happy
	zoe	thinking	It was this little silly idea I had, right? Almost like a creative exercise: can I turn the not-so-popular Liam into the center of a compelling story?
	zoe	epiphany	And then... ka-boom!
	player	affirming	Liams... Liams everywhere!	Player_bench_hehe
	zoe	happy	Haha, totally! The initial scope of this idea was so small... and now, the sky's the limit.
	zoe	default	It started as a fanfic with some art to depict the Liams, but lately my inbox has been brimming with opportunities of all sorts:
	zoe	thinking	Plushies, a tabletop roleplaying game set in Liam Academy, multiple offers to turn "Liam Prom" into a video game...
	player	surprised	Whoa! Say yes to everything! Sign all the deals! Next stop: "Liam Prom" pizza restaurants and Liam-themed lingerie!
	zoe	veryhappy	That'd be hilarious, wouldn't it?	Zex_laugh
	zoe	suspicious	But I'm always a bit wary. The bigger you become and the more stuff you sign... the more you gotta abide by what others expect from you.
	zoe	sad	It makes me think of April.
	zoe	thinking	I sometimes worry about her... with the whole contract thing, always having to be camera-ready...
	zoe	sad	I wonder if fame is that important in the end...
	zoe	sad	It took me eons to find my truth, so it's a shame to see someone who's contractually obliged not to show theirs.
	player	sorry	Yeah... when you put it like that...	Player_bench_yeah
	zoe	thinking	Of course it's not the same. It's gotta be ten times harder when you are your own brand, like how it is for April.
	player	asking	Have you talked to her? It feels like you could help each other out, since you're going through stuff that's similar in some ways.
	zoe	thinking	You're right, maybe I can do that later...
	zoe	happy	...it's just that I wanted to talk to you too. I really value your perspective.
	player	smilinginlove	That means a lot, really.
	narrator		And so, you spend some hours on this, helping Zoe surmise what she really wants, and the best parts of all these opportunities she's been given.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_5
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			How's Spooky Con so far?
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	happy	It's my second year here, and I can confirm: it's a dream come true.	Z_breathtaking
	zoe	pumped	It's not just that there's a whole lot of panels and activities I LOOOOVE.
	zoe	suggestive	There's something else...
	player	teasing	The total disintegration of any semblance of a personal space?
	zoe	happy	Haha, no, you silly!	Zex_laugh
	zoe	thinking	I couldn't put my finger on it until the other day, talking to Doug.
	zoe	default	He explained that he and April used to be the "nerdy ones" at their school.
	zoe	epiphany	Then it hit me: it was like that!
	zoe	nostalgic	I love everyone at Spooky Academy, but there, I was the nerdy one.
	zoe	thinking	Sure, some of our friends like anime or video games, but not to my degree of obsession.
	player	animesweat	Hehe, it can be hard to match your level of passion!	Player_bench_hehe
	zoe	pumped	Totally... and yet, there's places like this where... EVERYONE DOES?!
	player	default
	zoe	default	Take the other day: I spent most of the day roaming the con with Nico.
	zoe	thinking	We went to an anime premiere, to the artist alley, to some panels about our favorite video games...
	zoe	veryhappy	...and we were LOSING IT the whole time.	Z_squee
	zoe	happy	There was something magical in being with someone who could 100% match my energy.
	zoe	default	That doesn't mean I love my other friends any less. I love how different we can get to be and still connect.
	zoe	blush	But here, I feel like I've found something... something special.
	zoe	thinking	Does that make any sense?
	player	smilinginlove	Aw, Zoe, of course it does. That "something special" is a sense of belonging. And yes, it can feel like a magical thing.
	zoe	pumped	YES! It's exactly that, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%. Here, I feel like I'm among my people.
	zoe	default	It makes me so happy...
	player	affirming	And it makes me happy that it makes you happy!	Player_bench_metoo
	narrator		Zoe proceeds to explain the next twenty things she loves about the con. Her passion is legit electrifying.	

>>>	cdate_zoe_6
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	zoe
>action			The Spooky Con friend group
>layout	duo	zoe,player
	zoe	eyebrows	Ah, you want our friend-group's origin story, huh?	Zex_eyebrows
	player	affirming	You betcha!
	zoe	suggestive	Well, I won't be the one to deny backstory bits to the ones thirsting for lore.
	zoe	thinking	Omen is part of the Redemption Arc Program. They're dripping with lore, but I think it's better for them to share it, if they want.
	zoe	happy	Nico, I met through Liam.
	zoe	default	Then... there's Liam.
	zoe	pumped	We met as rivals on the annual Deadly Race of Death, where one hundred people race... but only one comes out alive!
	player	surprised	Wait... what? I thought...	Player_bench_questionwhat
	zoe	eyebrows	I'm kidding. We met at Spooky Academy, but that's kinda boring, so I have my own headcanon.	
	player	animesweat	Okay, fair.
	zoe	happy	Doug and I met through AO4. He was one of my first-ever readers. He left reassuring comments on everything I wrote.
	zoe	nostalgic	It really fueled me back then, you know? Even when you're writing for an audience of three or four, having constant support means the world.	Zex_dreamy
	zoe	default	We quickly built a great online friendship, as he loved many of the fandoms I wrote fanfics for.
	zoe	happy	Since "Liam Prom" became somewhat popular, he's offered to help me in any way he can, like keeping track of the lore or moderating my channels.
	zoe	blush	He's the kind of person you dream of having in your corner, really.
	player	lookingdown	Awww, that's sweet to hear.
	zoe	happy	It's just the truth.
	zoe	default	And finally, April... I met her through Doug.
	zoe	nostalgic	You know, it's great to meet another woman who's just now dealing with newfound fame, even if both our fames are... of moderate size.
	player	default	Yeah, I can imagine... you can be there for each other, truly understanding how it is.	Player_bench_makessense
	zoe	veryhappy	Gosh, so many amazing people, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%... becoming part of mortalkind was the right call.
	player	smilinginlove	I couldn't agree more, Zoe.
	narrator		You spend the rest of the night asking Zoe questions about the Deadly Race of Death and how both Liam and her survived it if only one racer can come alive.
	narrator		Who cares if it isn't canon? Her explanation is riveting!	

>>>	cdate_omen_1
