	omen	surprised	...
	omen	grumpy	Ugh, stupid smart Liam.	O_fuckinliam
	narrator		You spend the rest of the night plotting Omen's revenge on Liam for making them care about other people.	
	narrator		Still, you know that, deep down, they appreciate what Liam did.

>>>	cdate_omen_3
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	omen
>action			Hobbies
>layout	duo	omen,player
	omen	default	Eating hot dogs.	Oex_default
	player	embarrassed	That isn't a hobby.	Player_bench_questionwhat
	omen	confident	A pastime, then? It surely is a way in which I adore passing my time.
	player	surprised	You REALLY like hot dogs.
	omen	grumpy	I do. And one thing I do NOT like? Doctors. They keep telling me I should not eat so many hot dogs. Complete morons.	Oex_grumpy
	omen	laugh	Ah, hot dogs... hands-down, the best thing to happen to me after imprisonment.
	player	thinking	But, wait... aren't hot dogs a thing that has existed for more than a hundred years?
	player	asking	I'm pretty sure they were invented in Frankfurt in the late XVth century.
	player	yikes	(Dang... why does my brain retain these things but not my old passwords?)	Player_bench_yikes
	omen	talking	Do not beat yourself up, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%.
	omen	talking	Your brain isn't your greatest asset; but this is something we all have accepted by now. You should accept it too.
	player	thinking	Hmph... okay, but then how do you explain not knowing about hot dogs? They existed back then!
	omen	frustrated	Excuse me for not knowing about this one food during the 25 years I had before getting imprisoned.	O_shutup
	omen	default	This is the thing: the one thing we did NOT have back then was this internal net thing.
	omen	grumpy	So it was pretty plausible for people not to know about a certain thing if it didn't happen in your vicinity.
	omen	disgust	For example, I did not know about the existence of karate either.
	player	thinking	Huh, that makes sense.	Player_bench_makessense
	player	default
	omen	confident	It does; but then again, your brain isn't your best asset, as previously stated. It follows that it doesn't process common sense very well.
	omen	confident	It's a bit of a tragedy.
	omen	angry	And you want to know another tragedy? That I've come to know about hot dogs when I have half the hands I used to have.
	player	blush	...I could use one of mine to help you stuff hot dogs into your mouth.
	omen	surprised	Would you do that? Really? I would owe you a big one.	Oex_surprised
	player	animesweat	Don't mention it.
	omen	blush	Sorry for being mean to you, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%. You might have a weak brain, but you make up for it with a strong heart.
	player	blush	Eh... thanks.
	narrator		You run to the hot dog food truck, where you proceed to feed hot dogs to Omen. It's nice to spend time with your friends, trying out their hobbies.	

>>>	cdate_omen_4
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	omen
>action			Getting used to the modern world
>layout	duo	omen,player
	omen	frustrated	Hmph... don't get me started on that!	Oex_frustrated
	omen	disgust	Monsterkind should re-assess whether or not the world needs this many inventions.
	omen	angry	Vacuum-powered cleaners, machines that condition the air, mops... I can't keep up with all that.
	omen	default	It would feel less impossible if I could get some sort of weekly newsletter in my email explaining a bunch of inventions each time.
	player	surprised	Wait... how the heck do you know about email and newsletters but not A/C and mops?
	omen	talking	What's so hard to comprehend, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%?
	omen	talking	If you have more than a century's worth of progress to learn about, you might end up learning it out of order.
	player	thinking	Fair point.	Player_bench_makessense
	omen	default	Also, Liam got me this phone the other day. It's supposed to help me, since I can "look up" stuff on the internal net.
	omen	talking	Still, it's taking me weeks to understand how it works. Liam explained it, but I tend to block out his "Liam noises".
	omen	blush	I don't want to admit this defeat to him, so I've been doing research at the library.
	omen	grumpy	It is the worst punishment ever to be inflicted upon me.	Oex_grumpy
	player	yikes	...Is it?
	player	animesweat	Anyway, I'm sure you'll eventually realize all this learning is worth your time.
	player	affirming	Cause in the end, these inventions you have to learn about are useful and makes our lives easier!
	omen	angry	Well, not mine!
	omen	disgust	Take that grotesque nightmare that are revolving doors...
	omen	rage	What do they help? What was not working with regular doors to start with?!	Oex_rage
	player	embarrassed	Okay, MOST of these inventions are useful and make our lives easier.
	omen	frustrated	Stupid present times...
	omen	surprised	...
	omen	blush	%CURRENTPLAYERNAME%...
	omen	mischievous	Would you be down to strategize a plan for wiping out... let's say, 30% of the last century's progress with me?	O_mwahaha
	player	yikes	Eh... I'd rather not.
	player	affirming	What if, instead, I help you learn all about these "modern inventions"? We could start with your phone!
	narrator		Omen likes the idea. You spend the next few hours helping them set up an email so they can receive newsletters.	
	narrator		Teaching Omen is exhausting, but it's definitely worth your time.

>>>	cdate_omen_5
>event_type	conversational
>conversational_type	stage1
>conversational_npc	omen
>action			What does she miss from her previous life
>layout	duo	omen,player
