	omen	angry	They took my power; my might.	Oex_angry
	player	thinking	Your arm too.
	omen	default	Ah, yes, true.
	omen	frustrated	But losing a hand is losing a hand, while losing all your magic power? That's like losing a hundred different hands.
	omen	grumpy	Still, not cool they took my good hand.
	omen	mischievous	Note to myself: next time, harness my magic power in my bad hand.
	player	embarrassed	...What next time would that be?	Player_bench_questionwhat
	omen	talking	I don't know... next time.
	omen	laugh	The important thing here is that I can still beat someone to a pulp with one fist.
	omen	grumpy	I don't have such alternatives for my magical energy.
	omen	frustrated	It confuses me to see someone as mighty as Zoe forfeiting most of her power willingly.
	player	lookingdown	Yeah, she did that, didn't she?	Player_bench_yeah
	omen	angry	Zoe, who used to be one of the most powerful entities reality has ever seen; a deity of destruction and despair!
	omen	laugh	I used to dream of attaining the might of an Old One, or perhaps to murder one with my bare hands.
	omen	disgust	And what does she do with that? She writes tales of an academy infested with Liams who spend their time kissing each other.	O_justwhy
	omen	default	Huh... note to myself: investigate if this is a veiled stratagem by Zoe to bring despair to reality without people noticing.
	player	affirming	Give it a chance! It really hooks you once you get to chapter 5.	Player_bench_nice
	omen	frustrated	(Add to note: research if %CURRENTPLAYERNAME% is too far gone, brainwashed by Zoe's plan for mass despair.)
	player	thinking	Nah, but I think there's something to learn from Zoe here.
	player	affirming	Life has many things to offer beyond raw power. Maybe this is a blessing in disguise; maybe now you get to explore those things.
	omen	surprised	Uhm... could it be that these "things" are actually... worthwhile? If Zoe forfeited god-like powers in exchange for them, they must be of great value.	O_fascinating
	player	smilinginlove	I'd say they're priceless, Omen.
	narrator		Omen asks you to produce a list of at least ten of these "things" they can explore. You comply and offer to help them with it.	

>>>	cdate_omen_6
